<p>Xbox Play Anywhere games, as I'm sure you know, are games that you buy once and can play on PC and Xbox and <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/rog-xbox-ally-x-review">the new handheld ROG Ally X</a>, all within the Xbox-branded ecosystem. So if you were to buy Baldur's Gate 3 as an Xbox Play Anywhere game, you'd be able to chop and change where you play.</p><p>I'm not sure how it works retroactively, and whether if you already own the game on Xbox you'd be able to go back and play on a different platform, but I presume that'll be the case. I don't see why you'd punish earlier adopters of the game.</p>
<p>Baldur's Gate 3 remains one of the finest role-playing games of this generation, and it's a game that's been heavily updated by Larian since it was released in 2023. <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/baldurs-gate-3s-last-ever-major-update-gets-a-long-awaited-release-date">The final BG3 patch, Patch 8</a>, released in the spring, brought cross-play, new subclasses, a photo mode, and the long-awaited addition of split-screen co-op on Xbox Series S. In short, if you haven't played it, do.</p>

